abstract: NASA says unmanned Falcon 9 rocket heading for International Space Station with cargo disintegrated several minutes after launching from Cape Canaveral Air Force Station in Florida; destruction of SpaceX rocket raises questions on how station will continue to be supplied.
lead_paragraph: The unmanned Falcon 9 rocket, built by Space Exploration Technologies, was destined for the International Space Station with a load of cargo.

headline.main: SpaceX Rocket Breaks Apart After Launch to Space Station
headline.print_headline: SpaceX Rocket Falls Apart on Way to Space Station
